postcontent:
Up for sale today we have a Suomi M31.  This is a 9mm carbine that was imported and converted by TNW.  The barrel shroud and barrel remove with the simple turning of a latch and rotation of the two pieces.  This makes cleaning a breeze.

Included with the rifle are two stick magazines.  These each hold 36 rounds.  I am also including three drum magazines that each hold 71 rounds.  I also have two pouches that hold the drum magazines nicely. 

This thing is a tad on the heavy side compared to modern rifles, but it has the recoil of a .22 and is a blast to shoot.  I have only put about 50 rounds down the pipe on this one.

Based on the Finnish Military Rifle, this is a historic rebuild of the Finnish M31 Suomi. Designed by Aimo Johannes Lahti in the late 1920s, the Suomi was instrumental in defending Finland against the Soviet invasion during the Winter War of 1939-40 and Continuation War from 1941-44.

Features a new US made 16.25in barrel, parkerized finish, and a wooden stock. The firearm is made from a mix of original used Finnish parts, and new US made parts.

title: For Sale/Trade:  H&K VP70 9mm with 7 18 round mags
postcontent: The Heckler & Koch VP70 is a double-action only polymer-framed pistol made by German small arms manufacturer Heckler & Koch GmbH. The name VP70 stands for Vollautomatische Pistole 1970, referring to its automatic fire capability. Alternatively, VP70 stands for Volks Pistole 1970. Chambered for the 9x19mm cartridge, the VP70 was the first commercially available handgun with a polymer frame, predating the more successful Glock 17 by over a decade. The VP70 came in two variants, the VP70Z and VP70M. The VP70Z was a civilian model that could only fire in semiautomatic mode. The VP70M was made for military forces and had a three-round burst fire mode, as well as a detachable butt stock. Production ended in 1989 and the VP70 was later replaced by the USP in the early 1990s. The pistol comes in a H&K box (not original box) and comes with seven 18 round original magazines. title: For Sale/Trade:  H&K VP70 9mm with 7 18 round mags
postcontent: The Heckler & Koch VP70 is a double-action only polymer-framed pistol made by German small arms manufacturer Heckler & Koch GmbH. The name VP70 stands for Vollautomatische Pistole 1970, referring to its automatic fire capability. Alternatively, VP70 stands for Volks Pistole 1970. Chambered for the 9x19mm cartridge, the VP70 was the first commercially available handgun with a polymer frame, predating the more successful Glock 17 by over a decade. The VP70 came in two variants, the VP70Z and VP70M. The VP70Z was a civilian model that could only fire in semiautomatic mode. The VP70M was made for military forces and had a three-round burst fire mode, as well as a detachable butt stock. Production ended in 1989 and the VP70 was later replaced by the USP in the early 1990s. The pistol comes in a H&K box (not original box) and comes with seven 18 round original magazines. It will also come with a reduced pull trigger spring that reduces the pull by approx 5 lbs
